data.title: Wellington School of Business and Government Dean’s List
data.meta_description: The Dean's List is a formal record of our undergraduate students who achieve academic excellence.
data.text:
The Dean's List is a formal record of our undergraduate students who achieve academic excellence.

To qualify for the Dean’s List, students must have:

completed at least 100 points of study towards one or more undergraduate degrees over the course of an academic year

achieved a GPA of 7.5 of higher across the courses they take

passed every course they take that year.

The Dean’s List Policy has more detailed information about the selection process.
